## Frequently Asked Questions (FAQ)

### What is the average interest rate for SME loans in Malaysia?
For banks, it ranges from 5% to 9%. For credit companies, it can be 8% to 15% depending on the risk and the type of equipment being financed.

### Can I get a business loan if my company is only 1 year old?
Yes, but you likely won't get it from a traditional bank. Credit companies like Ing Heng Credit are much more open to businesses with 1-2 years of track record, especially for equipment-backed loans.

### What documents do I need for an SME loan?
At minimum: SSM (Full set), 6 months bank statements, IC of directors, and a quotation for the equipment you want to buy (if it's an equipment loan).

### How much can I borrow?
Most lenders will look at your monthly credit turnover. Usually, they won't lend you more than 3-4 times your average monthly credit balance unless you have significant collateral.

